ics|Green Politics]] {{cn|date=December 2019}}\n|2003\n|0\n|-\n|[[Puerto Rican Independence Party]]\n|[[Independence movement in Puerto Rico|Puerto Rico independence]] {{cn|date=December 2019}}\n|1946\n|0\n|-\n|[[Working People's Party of Puerto Rico]]\n|[[Democratic socialism|Democratic Socialism]] {{cn|date=December 2019}}\n|2010\n|0\n|-\n|[[Moderate Party of Rhode Island]]\n|[[Centrism]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121112082226/http://rhodeisland.onpolitix.com/parties/7/moderate-party|title=Moderate Party {{!}} Rhode Island {{!}} onPolitix|date=2012-11-12|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref>\n|2007\n|0\n|-\n|[[American Party of South Carolina|Alliance Party of South Carolina]]\n|[[Centrism]] {{cn|date=December 2019}}\n|2014\n|0\n|-\n|[[United Citizens Party]]\n|[[Progressivism]] {{cn|date=December 2019}}\n|1969\n|0\n|-\n|[[United Utah Party]]\n|[[Centrism]] {{cn|date=December 2019}}\n|2017\n|0\n|-\n|[[Independent Citizens Movement]]\n|[[Grassroots democracy|Grassroots Democracy]] {{cn|date=December 2019}}\n|1968\n|0\n|-\n|[[Liberty Union Party]]\n|[[Democratic socialism]]{{cn|date=December 2019}}\n|1970\n|0\n|-\n|[[Independent Greens of Virginia]]\n|[[Green politics|Green Politics]]{{cn|date=December 2019}}\n|2005\n|0\n|-\n|[[Progressive Dane]]\n|[[Progressivism]] {{cn|date=December 2019}}\n|1992\n|0\n|-\n|[[Working Class Party]]\n|[[Progressivism]]{{cn|date=December 2019}}\n|2016\n|0\n|}\n\n== Historical parties ==\n:''The following parties are no longer functioning.''\n<!--\nWhile there were political movements such as [[Anti-Federalism]] and [[Federalism (United States)|Federalism]] in the 1780s, these were not organized groups and therefore do not meet the definition of political party.\n-->\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Historical parties in the United States\n! Name !! Other names !! Established !! Disbanded\n|-\n| [[Federalist Party]] || || 1789 || 1820\n|-\n| [[Anti-Administration party]] || || 1789 || 1792\