{"title_page": "James B. Bell", "text_new": "{{Infobox military person\n|name          = James B. Bell\n|birth_date    = {{birth date|1835|08|09}}\n|death_date    = {{death date and age|1910|06|30|1835|08|09}}\n|birth_place   = Branot, [[Ohio]]\n|death_place   = \n|placeofburial = [[Gettysburg, Ohio]]\n|allegiance    = {{flag|United States of America|1861}}\n|branch        = {{army|USA}}\n|serviceyears  = \n|rank          = Sergeant\n|unit          = {{Flagicon|Ohio}} [[11th Regiment Ohio Volunteer Infantry]] - Company H\n|battles       = [[Battle of Missionary Ridge]]\n|awards        = {{Flagicon image|Medal of Honor ribbon.svg}} [[Medal of Honor]]\n}}\n\n'''James Bennett Bell''' (August 9, 1835 \u2013 June 30, 1910) was an [[United States|American]] soldier who fought in the [[American Civil War]] and a recipient of the U.S. military's highest decoration, the [[Medal of Honor]], for his actions at the [[Battle of Missionary Ridge]] on November 25, 1863.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://valor.militarytimes.com/hero/1531 |title=Military Times Hall of Valor |accessdate=14 September 2013}}</ref>\n\nBell died on June 30, 1910 and is buried in [[Gettysburg, Ohio]].<ref>{{cite web|title=James Bennett Bell|publisher=Find a Grave|date=30 January 2004|accessdate=14 September 2013|url=https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/8335054}}</ref>\n\n==Medal of Honor citation==\n{{quotation|Though severely wounded, was first of his regiment on the summit of the ridge, planted his colors inside the enemy's works, and did not leave the field until after he had been wounded five times.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bell, James B.|url=http://www.cmohs.org/recipient-detail/86/bell-james-b.php|publisher=Congressional Medal of Honor Society|accessdate=14 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.history.army.mil/html/moh/civwaral.html |title=Civil War (A-L) Medal of Honor Recipients |accessdate=14 September 2013}}</ref>}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Biography|American Civil War}}\n*[[List of American Civil War Medal of Honor recipients: A\u2013F]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Belcher, Thomas}}\n[[Category:1835 births]]\n[[Category:1910 deaths]]\n[[Category:People of Ohio in the American Civil War]]\n[[Category:Union Army soldiers]]\n[[Category:United States Army Medal of Honor recipients]]\n[[Category:American Civil War recipients of the Medal of Honor]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox military person\n|name          = James B. Bell\n|birth_date    = {{birth date|1835|08|09}}\n|death_date    = {{death date and age|1910|06|30|1835|08|09}}\n|birth_place   = Branot, [[Ohio]]\n|death_place   = \n|placeofburial = [[Gettysburg, Ohio]]\n|allegiance    = {{flag|United States of America|1861}}\n|branch        = {{army|USA}}\n|serviceyears  = \n|rank          = Sergeant\n|unit          = {{Flagicon|Ohio}} Company H, [[11th Ohio Infantry]]\n|battles       = [[Battle of Missionary Ridge]]\n|awards        = {{Flagicon image|Medal of Honor ribbon.svg}} [[Medal of Honor]]\n}}\n\n'''James Bennett Bell''' (August 9, 1835 \u2013 June 30, 1910) was an [[United States|American]] soldier who fought in the [[American Civil War]] and a recipient of the U.S. military's highest decoration, the [[Medal of Honor]], for his actions at the [[Battle of Missionary Ridge]] on November 25, 1863.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://valor.militarytimes.com/hero/1531 |title=Military Times Hall of Valor |accessdate=14 September 2013}}</ref>\n\nBell died on June 30, 1910 and is buried in [[Gettysburg, Ohio]].<ref>{{cite web|title=James Bennett Bell|publisher=Find a Grave|date=30 January 2004|accessdate=14 September 2013|url=https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/8335054}}</ref>\n\n==Medal of Honor citation==\n{{quotation|Though severely wounded, was first of his regiment on the summit of the ridge, planted his colors inside the enemy's works, and did not leave the field until after he had been wounded five times.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bell, James B.|url=http://www.cmohs.org/recipient-detail/86/bell-james-b.php|publisher=Congressional Medal of Honor Society|accessdate=14 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.history.army.mil/html/moh/civwaral.html |title=Civil War (A-L) Medal of Honor Recipients |accessdate=14 September 2013}}</ref>}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Biography|American Civil War}}\n*[[List of American Civil War Medal of Honor recipients: A\u2013F]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Belcher, Thomas}}\n[[Category:1835 births]]\n[[Category:1910 deaths]]\n[[Category:People of Ohio in the American Civil War]]\n[[Category:Union Army soldiers]]\n[[Category:United States Army Medal of Honor recipients]]\n[[Category:American Civil War recipients of the Medal of Honor]]\n", "name_user": "Hhfjbaker", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_B._Bell"}
